bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as amiable, genuine, and considerate.

In my spare time, I like to cook with friends, exercise, and journal.

Hello! My name is Emma, and I recently graduated from Washington and Lee University and moved to Atlanta to work for an NGO.

I've been working with children of all ages since high school, and have childcare experience babysitting for families, leading groups of children in Sunday School, at summer camp, during Vacation Bible School, and more. I am Red Cross certified for infant, child, and adult first aid. I also have 2 years of tutoring experience, and I am confidently prepared to tutor in reading comprehension and English skills, writing, basic math, and Spanish. I also scored a 35 on my ACT and have experience and strategies to tutor for ACT preparation. 

Whether tutoring or simply caring for children, I strive to make sure our activities are educational, fun, and age appropriate. I am friendly, energetic, adaptable, and love to work with infants and children of all ages! I'm good with pets as well, and am available for evening babysitting after work and on weekends.

Hi! My name is Kadia, I'm currently a college student majoring in nursing and minoring in psychology. I am now a Registered Behavioral Therapist working with kids with autism, ADHD, etc. I've been taking care of kids for about 8 years now. I started off babysitting my nieces & nephews and eventually began babysitting kids in my neighborhood. I also have experience working at a daycare. I can truly say that I enjoy taking care of children. Which is why I decided to become a neonatal nurse once I graduate college. This is something that I am genuinely passionate about.

description.displayText: Kadia is a very pleasant young lady. She was punctual and professional and did amazing with my two children! I would definitely hire her again as well as highly recommend her.
description.originalText: Kadia is a very pleasant young lady. She was punctual and professional and did amazing with my two children! I would definitely hire her again as well as highly recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary: I have volunteered for multiple years in child care and had multiple babysitting roles. I have a car as well as an incredible work ethic. I would be more than happy to help out with household chores such as laundry, vacuuming, and light cleaning! I look forward to hearing back and answering any questions you might have.

As a dedicated childcare provider with a decade of experience, my passion lies in nurturing young minds and fostering their holistic development. My patient and friendly demeanor creates a welcoming environment where children feel safe and supported. I prioritize open communication with parents, using their preferred method to discuss their child's daily experiences and address any concerns promptly. By following the parents' lead on household rules, I ensure a consistent and respectful approach to discipline.

Holding a graduate degree in mental health counseling and having completed coursework in early child development, I continuously enhance my skills to provide the best possible care.

What sets me apart is my genuine love for children and my unwavering commitment to their well-being.

Hi there! 
My name is Amanda and I just graduated with my Masters in Physician Assistant Studies. I would love to get back to babysitting/nannying until I start my new job as an Emergency Medicine PA in May of 2024. I am comfortable with children of all ages and I am BLS/ACLS certified. I am certainly a kid at heart still so I love playing outside and forming relationships with kids. I would love to become a part of your family, whether that be part-time or full-time!

description.displayText: Amanda is great with my son and he adores her!  She has been a huge help.  I highly recommend her.
description.originalText: Amanda is great with my son and he adores her!  She has been a huge help.  I highly recommend her.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm an empathetic childcare provider with a deep-rooted passion for nurturing the growth and development of young minds. My journey in this field began with fulfilling babysitting experiences that solidified my desire to make a positive impact on children's lives.

My approach to childcare is centered around patience, creativity, and fostering a friendly environment. I believe in open communication with parents, ensuring that they are well-informed about their child's day and any matters that arise. I'm also comfortable enforcing household rules to maintain a safe and structured environment.

With my background in Early Childhood Education and Early Child Development, I'm equipped with the knowledge and skills necessary to provide high-quality care. I enjoy engaging children in various activities, from outdoor games and puzzles to educational games that stimulate their learning.

I am allergic to pets so I would love to join assist your pet free household.

I'm passionate about helping children thrive and aspire to open my own childcare center. With over 7 years of experience and a deep love for children, I ensure that each child receives personalized care and attention. I'm patient, creative, and friendly, and I believe that open communication with parents is crucial. I follow their lead when enforcing household rules and keep them updated about their child's day. Whether it's outdoor games, board games, puzzles, or educational games, I love engaging children in fun activities that promote learning and development. With my skills and experience, I'm confident that I can provide a safe and nurturing environment for your child.

As a caregiver for over two decades, my passion lies in nurturing children's growth and development. My journey began with fulfilling babysitting experiences that ignited a desire to positively impact young lives. With my patient and calm demeanor, I create a serene environment for children to thrive.

My creativity and imagination shine through as I engage children in outdoor sports, board games, puzzles, and educational games that foster learning. I ensure open communication with parents through daily written reports and verbal updates at pickup, adapting to their preferred communication style.

My unwavering commitment to childcare excellence is underscored by my certifications in First Aid and CPR, as well as my experience with special needs children. As a Certified Teacher with Child Development Associate (CDA) credentials and a solid foundation in Early Child Development coursework, I bring a wealth of knowledge and expertise to my caregiving role.

description.originalText: Tyeicha is such an amazing nanny.  My kids absolutely love her.  She is reliable, dependable, and trustworthy.  You can tell she is very experienced and she has a passion caring for children.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm Kadie. I was born and raised in Steamboat Springs, Colorado. After I graduated high school, I lived in Champaign, IL for two years earning my Associate of Arts Degree in Psychology at Parkland College. Then I finished with my Bachelor of Arts Degree in Psychology at Flagler College, in St. Augustine, FL. I also spent time living in Los Angeles and St. Louis. In all of my moves I have had the pleasure of working for multiple families and two home daycares. Now, I am living in Atlanta, GA! I've been here about 6 months now, so I'm kinda new, but it's been great exploring what the city has to offer. I am seeking a wonderful family who is looking for the perfect nanny to care for their kiddos! Child care is a passion of mine and every new family holds a special place in my heart!

description.displayText: My family loves Kadie. She fit right in to our tribe & I always knew my son was in superb hands. She is fun, kind, sweet & loving. My 3 year old son would often tell me how much fun he has with her. They spent lots of time outdoors, which my son loved!!!! He also loved her sweet pup. I enjoyed her being around & I valued her time, energy & care. Kadie is a top pick. I feel so grateful & blessed to have had her as our nanny. She's incredible in all the ways.
